# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to run in multiple environments; otherwise, check them in:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different OS, you may ignore this file.
#  Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   This is especially important for applications to ensure all environments deploy with the exact same dependencies.
#   However, you can choose to ignore it if you run into environment mismatches.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include pdm.lock in version control.
# pdm.lock
#   pdm build stage
.pdm-build/

# venv
#   Recommended to not include virtual environment directory in github
.env
.venv
env/
venv/
ENV/
env.bak/
venv.bak/
.conda/

